OL,3,CDanger of 'crying wolf' if flood
OL,4,Cwarnings are made too often, says NRW
OL,6,F"Public organisations are there to
OL,7,Fserve, but people also need to take
OL,8,Fsome personal ownership of it. It's
OL,9,Fnot a pleasant or easy thing to say,
OL,10,Fbut it's the reality. What I'm not
OL,11,Fsaying there is (that) they need to
OL,12,Fsort it out themselves. That's totally
OL,13,Fnot what I'm saying. But they need to
OL,14,Frecognise that the risk is there."
OL,16,FSimon Brown, Service Director at the
OL,17,FMet Office, was asked if his
OL,18,Forganisation's weather warnings, used
OL,19,Fby NRW to make its own warnings, were
OL,20,Fclear enough.
